Work for the SFISD: Immediate Jobs Available

1) Bus Driver: The SFISD is seeking a competent individual to drive a school bus. Must possess or be able to possess a CDL with passenger and school endorsements. SFISD will reimburse expenses for CDL if employed by the district. 100% insurance provided by the district through TSHBP or TRS-Active Care. Please contact Mr. Keeney at rkeeney@sfisd.net

2. Food Service: The SFISD is seeking a competent individual to work in the food service department. Great insurance and benefit plans. Please contact Mrs. Hayes at khayes@sfisd.net.

Both positions require State fingerprinting and a GED or higher educational merit. Bus drivers are subject to drug and alcohol testing.

To apply, click: https://sanfordfritch.tedk12.com/hire/index.aspx

INFORMATION: Athletic Event Tickets

Lady Eagle Volleyball Games: All home game tickets will be sold at the gate. Away game ticket information will be posted as soon as we receive notice from the opposing schools.

Eagle Football Tickets: Tickets for all home games and all district games home and away will be pre-sold on M-Th BEFORE the actual game date. Tickets will be available at the HS office. You are encouraged to get your tickets early to avoid social distancing issues at the gate. Tickets may or may not be available at the gate at home games.

SCHOOL BUS INFORMATION FOR PARENTS:
Parents/Guardians: Due to COVID-19 and a shortage of personnel, the SFISD administration encourages you to personally bring your children to school or find alternative solutions to ensure the safety of your children. The SFISD cannot guarantee that social distancing can be achieved on the buses. Remember that all students 10 and up are required to wear a mask; however, it is recommended that all students wear a mask while traveling on a school bus. We are working on this issue but again we cannot guarantee social distancing on school buses. If you have any questions, contact Mr. McClellan at eagles@sfisd.net or (806) 397-0159.

üîµ PLEASE READ: IMPORTANT INFORMATION üîµ
Parents/Guardians: This survey is part of the new SFISD COVID-19 registration process. It's very important that you take the time to complete the survey as accurately and quickly as possible. This will assist the district in providing the best solution to the educational needs of your child. We will need your name and the name of your children with the grade level listed for each child.
Please understand that a commitment is based on a six-week grading period. You can change curriculum's but only at the beginning of a grading period.
Per SFISD Board Resolution: On-campus instruction will allow a student to participate in extracurricular activities; online instruction will not allow students to participate in extracurricular activities.
Only complete the survey once. If you realize a mistake has been made after submission, please contact Mr. McClellan at 806-397-0159 or email eagles@sfisd.net. Thank You!

Link to survey: https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/SFISD

post_text:
April is Child Abuse Prevention Month

It began when a report about abused and neglected children caught the attention of President Ronald Reagan in 1983. Sadly, since that first Child Abuse Prevention Month, the number of abused victims has grown from half a million children to over six million new reports of abuse along with 1600 child abuse related deaths annually.

One is too many. One in four girls and one in six boys will be sexually abused before their 18th birthday. Most child abuse incidents are drug and alcohol related. Within one year of aging out of the foster care system, 66% of victims will be homeless, in jail or dead. There are over 100,000 children waiting for adoption in the United States.

Pray they will be rescued
Pray they are placed with caring people
Pray their minds and bodies can heal
Pray they find hope
Pray for those who rescue them

IMPORTANT UPDATE: Governor Abbott has closed ALL schools through April 3, 2020. At this time, SFISD will begin classes on April 6, 2020. The administration is working diligently to provide instruction for the students during this time. More information in regards to instruction will be posted later.
SFISD will begin serving breakfast and lunch next Wednesday to qualifying kids under the Federal Free and Reduced program. Look for more information on Monday.
Again, please be patient with us as we work toward providing the best for our school and community.

SFISD Administration is asking all parents of students of the SFISD to complete the following survey so the district can make informed decisions on how best to serve our students should the district have to close beyond next week due to the Coronavirus. post_text:
Texas Abuse Hotline Information
www.txabusehotline.org
1-800-252-5400

Call the Texas Abuse Hotline when the situation is urgent. Urgent means someone faces an immediate risk of abuse or neglect that could result in death or serious harm. Call when situations include but are not limited to: Serious injuries, any injury to a child, immediate need for medical treatment (including suicidal thoughts), sexual abuse where the abuser has or will have access to the victim within the next 24 hours, children age five and under are alone or are likely to be left alone within the next 24 hours, and anytime you believe your situation requires action in less than 24 hours

January 9 at 7:00 AM ¬∑

We are watching the potential for snowfall to move across parts of the Panhandle Friday into Friday night. Current forecast shows snow starting in the NW early Friday afternoon and moving southeast into the evening and overnight hours on Friday. This is a tricky forecast so please check back for updates. If the main system moves north, we could be dry slotted with little to no snow. So please check back often for updates as we get closer to Friday.

US National Weather Service Amarillo Texas
November 20, 2019 at 7:45 AM ¬∑

645am 11/20: Snow appears likely for the northwestern Panhandles Thursday night. The far southern and southeastern Texas Panhandle are expected to largely experience a cold rain, but a brief change to wintry precipitation cannot be ruled out. In between, cold rain may change over to snow and/or freezing drizzle overnight. No matter what exactly falls out of the sky, the main impact from this round of precipitation is expected to be slick roadways, in particular bridges and overpasses.

US National Weather Service Amarillo Texas
October 22, 2019 at 4:00 PM ¬∑

We are watching a storm system Wednesday night through Thursday night that is currently expected to bring a good dose of cold air, wind, and a little precipitation to the Panhandles. The current forecast track for the system keeps most of the moisture south of the Panhandles, and therefore keeps rain/snow chances low. That being said, the area could see brief rain turning to snow, but accumulations are expected to be light, if any. The one exception to this is in the far northwest combined Panhandles where 0.5" to 2.0" of snow is possible.

There is some potential for this storm system to slow down, dive further south and strengthen more than currently forecast. In this case, rain/snow chances would increase with increased wind and colder temperatures.

Stay tuned as the forecast is refined!

STAFF CHANGES AT SFISD: The SFISD will see new faces in new places beginning October 1, 2019.

Mrs. Edie Allen will be moving from the Elementary to the Administration Office. She will serve the district as the Assistant Superintendent and District Coordinator for School Improvement. Mrs. Kim Surles will move from Assistant Principal of the High School to Principal of the Elementary.

Both moves were approved and supported by the SFISD Board of Trustees. "Mrs. Allen will have the responsibility of increasing our accountability scores on all three campuses" said SFISD Superintendent Jim McClellan. "Mrs. Surles is an up and coming administrator and will do a great job at the Elementary", McClellan added.

Texas Department of Public Safety - Southeast Texas Region
August 9, 2019 at 2:05 PM ¬∑

A STOPPED SCHOOL BUS: WHAT DO I DO?

Texas State law requires that drivers stop when a school bus is operating a visual signal-either red flashing lights or extended stop arm (TRC 545.066). However, many Texas drivers are uncertain as to when they need to stop for a school bus.

Here are a few guidelines to reduce driver confusion, thus providing a safer environment for our children. #BackToSchoolSafety

post_text: The Sanford-Fritch ISD Administration notified at approximately 9:30 a.m. by the Amarillo Police Department that two District buses with approximately 80 elementary students on board were involved in an accident in downtown Amarillo while on field trip. Emergency authorities at the scene reported 2 students with minor injuries, and one employee with more significant injuries. These individual have been transported to Northwest Hospital in Amarillo for further assessment, and their families have been notified. The other students and adults are receiving care at a nearby church. Those with possible injuries will be evaluated and transported to the hospital at the direction of emergency authorities at the scene. The District will continue to cooperate with emergency authorities and coordinate for the care of all involved. The Superintendent is now on his way to Northwest Texas Hospital. The District will provide further information to families as it becomes available.

post_text: Sanford-Fritch Elementary is accepting Pre-Kindergarten and Kindergarten student enrollment for students new to the district for the 2019-2020 school year. To enroll, parents or guardians will need to provide a current driver's license along with the student's birth certificate, current shot record, official social security card and proof of residency (current within the last 30 days utility bill or current lease). Stop by the office at 201 N. Hoyne and pick up an enrollment packet between 8:00 am and 4:00 pm. Monday through Friday. Current PK students already enrolled need not re-enroll.

SFISD Board Briefs: The SFISD Board of Trustees met Monday, March 18, 2019. Several items of interest to the SFISD community were discussed:

1) The SFISD Activity Center fees will change beginning today, 3-19-19. The fee to join or renew for one year will go up from $10 to $30. Senior (65+) fees will remain at $10. This increase will go to repair damaged or stolen equipment or purchase newer equipment. Please note this fee is for one year not per month. Still a great deal!

2) The Board also approved an Order of Cancellation for the May elections. There will not be a school board trustee election in May.

If you have any questions, please contact Jim McClellan, SFISD Superintendent at 806-397-0159 Ext. 4 or email eagles@sfisd.net.
